CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1955, pg. 11 reads: "Breakfast on the Lawn - Min-Ceil Club breakfast, held on the spacious lawn of the Emmett F. Davisees of Lincoln Avenue, as usual was a scene of beauty last Sunday, when hundreds of fashionable socialites attended the annual outdoor affair. Here you see just a partial picture of the crowd which enjoyed a sumptuous breakfast and the wholesome fun of chatting with old and new friends at the event.- "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men and women, including one standing front center wearing dark hat with light colored ribbon and floral dress, gathered on the lawn of Emmett F. Davises home of Lincoln Avenue for the Min-Ceil Club breakfast lawn with large trees, tables and chairs, shade umbrella with striped underside on the left, and iron fence
